"headline": "Weight Stigma and Health Behaviors: New Research Findings",
"body": "Weight stigma is significantly associated with disordered eating, comfort eating, alcohol use, and sleep disturbance, according to a recent study. The research suggests that weight stigma can undermine health behaviors, regardless of BMI. The study also found that weight stigma affects individuals across the weight spectrum, not just those with overweight or obese BMIs. These findings highlight weight stigma as a potential barrier to healthy behaviors and emphasize the importance of reducing weight stigma in health promotion."
